qas.question: Ancestors of which tribes lived in Oklahoma?
What was Spiro, Oklahoma named for?
What Spanish explorer visited Oklahoma in 1541?
When did France sell Oklahoma's land to the US?

context: Evidence exists that native peoples traveled through Oklahoma as early as the last ice age. Ancestors of the <a0_0>Wichita and Caddo<a0_0/> lived in what is now Oklahoma. The Panhandle culture peoples were precontact residents of the panhandle region. The westernmost center of the Mississippian culture was <a1_0>Spiro Mounds<a1_0/>, in what is now Spiro, Oklahoma, which flourished <a2_0>between AD 850 and 1450<a2_0/>. Spaniard <a3_0>Francisco Vásquez de Coronado<a3_0/> traveled through the state in 1541, but French explorers claimed the area in the 1700s and it remained under French rule until <a4_0>1803<a4_0/>, when all the French territory west of the Mississippi River was purchased by the United States in the Louisiana Purchase.
